OL,3,CTV-related anniversaries for 23 MAY
OL,4,CMISCELLANEOUS
OL,5,
OL,6,CG1988FGay rights activists breach
OL,7,Fsecurity at BBC Television Centre and
OL,8,Fdisrupt the live transmission of the
OL,9,FSix o'Clock News on BBC One.
OL,10,
OL,11,FThe three women vocalised their
OL,12,Fopposition to Clause 28 during the
OL,13,Fopening minutes of the programme.
OL,14,FPresenter Nicholas Witchell placed his
OL,15,Fhand over the mouth of the most vocal
OL,16,Fprotestor, whilst Sue Lawley read the
OL,17,Fopening headlines.
OL,18,
OL,19,FLawley apologised for the disruption
OL,20,Fbefore linking into the first story,
OL,21,Ftelling viewers: "We have rather been
OL,22,Finvaded by some people who we hope to
